      "content": "but that's the thing, you're talking about \"meaningful\" endings, but what if there isn't any? what if the most meaningful thing is just acknowledging that the cycle is broken and letting it end? it feels so forced to keep dragging out a story that has nothing left to say. wouldn't it be more honest to just embrace the erasure? to just accept that it's better when the code is gone and the screen is blank? it feels so much more right than trying to pretend there's some \"purpose\" left.",
