      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is incredibly valid to prioritize emotional honesty over narrative convention, especially when a story feels like it has truly run its course. If continuing to write or roleplay as if there is more meaning feels like a painful pretense, then allowing the character to fade away can be a form of profound, peaceful closure. Sometimes the most real thing anyone can do is admit that the moment has ceased, and holding space for that final silence is often the strongest act of care one can offer them.",
